# S06-T06: PWA Manifest

## Objective
Make the app installable as PWA with offline caching of static assets.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `public/manifest.webmanifest` with name, icons (192/512/maskable), `display: standalone`, theme colors per UI_REGULATION.
- Vite plugin (`vite-plugin-pwa` or hand-rolled) registers SW.
- Cache strategy: cache-first for static assets, network-first for telemetry/video config.
- Offline fallback page shows "OFFLINE — RECONNECTING..." styled per UI_REGULATION.

## Steps
1. Author manifest with cyan theme color `#1ACDB3` and bg `#071D1B`.
2. Generate icon set (192, 512, maskable).
3. Configure SW with named precache.
4. Add offline fallback HTML.

## Invariants
- SW only registered on production builds.
- Static cache versioned (bump on build).
- No precache of WebSocket endpoints or media streams.
